===Etymology===
Greek; compare French ''[[polygamie]]''
=== Noun ===
#The having of a plurality of wives at the same time; usually, the marriage of a man to more than one woman, or the practice of having several wives, at the same time; -- opposed to [[monogamy]]; as, the nations of the East practiced '''polygamy'''. See the Note under [[bigamy]], and compare [[polyandry]] and [[polygyny]].
#''(Zoölogy):'' The state or habit of having more than one mate.
#''(Botany):'' The condition or state of a plant which bears both perfect and unisexual flowers.

